I'll calculate each financial metric step by step based on the provided financial statements.

## Free Cash Flow (FCF)
FCF = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities - Capital Expenditures
FCF = -64,099.10 - 528,936.17 = -593,035.27

## Return on Assets (ROA)
ROA = Net Income / Average Total Assets
Average Total Assets = (Initial Assets + End Assets) / 2 = (13,000,000 + 15,200,446.16) / 2 = 14,100,223.08
ROA = 707,199.17 / 14,100,223.08 = 0.0502 = 5.02%

## Return on Equity (ROE)
ROE = Net Income / Average Equity
Average Equity = (Initial Equity + End Equity) / 2 = (13,000,000 + 13,707,199.17) / 2 = 13,353,599.59
ROE = 707,199.17 / 13,353,599.59 = 0.0530 = 5.30%

## Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio
OCF to Net Income = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Net Income
OCF to Net Income = -64,099.10 / 707,199.17 = -0.09

## Net Profit Margin
Net Profit Margin = Net Income / Total Revenue
Net Profit Margin = 707,199.17 / 5,064,939.23 = 0.1396 = 13.96%

## Gross Profit Margin
Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue
Gross Profit Margin = 2,329,939.23 / 5,064,939.23 = 0.4600 = 46.00%
